        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 4:58PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Lewistown, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grass Range, Heath, and Forestgrove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
central Montana.</instruction>
